Product name: Stunning antique French Jacob Delafon bath shower mixer  faucet taps C1900
Description:
These are magnificent, and getting harder and harder to find, to be honest whenever I see antique fittings and faucets of this quality I buy them (curiously I have a penchant for antique bathroom fixtures, they were almost sculptural in design) these particular beauties were made by the grand daddy of French bathroom fixtures 'Jacob Delafon' his fittings were of the very finest quality and adorned the finest homes in France and they obviously command a very high price now on the salvage market.  I managed to get these taps at source for a song, so I am passing on my good fortune to someone who will revel in them as I do!
They really would MAKE a bathroom.  Wonderful quality. Heavy gauge brass with a nickel finish with beautiful porcelain inserts reading 
Chaud - Hot. 
Froid - Cold.
Bain - Bath
Douche - shower
They have the most amazing patina only acquired with great age, I find them utterly charming.
Condition report
I am selling them in 'as is' condition, there is wear and Verdi Gris to the finish.  They are untried and not tested, but all of the taps turn with ease.  With these older taps be prepared to do a little work, washers may need replacing etc.. But for this price you would struggle to get reproduction fixtures never mind original Jacob Delafon, so a compromise may have to be made.  I am just passing on my previous experience of antique bathroom ware, it is fitted throughout my home with no issues, but a little more care is required when fitting, but the finish is ABSOLUTELY worth it! 
You can actually have a look on YouTube, there are lots of videos on how to refurbish antique faucets, it's really not as hard as you imagine, I have personally just done a set of taps for a shower that leaked and needed new internal mechanisms (10 online) they now work like new. And all this info is worst case scenario as they have not been tested properly.
NB I do have some modern chromed elbow joints that fit these taps that I will include free of charge in the sale, you may not wish to use them, but your plumber will be very grateful as they will make fitting a lot easier and you won't have the trouble I had trying to find some.
Dimensions
8 1/2 " or 22cm high
11" or 28cm wide
8" or 20cm depth
7 1/2lbs or 3.4kg weight

Product name: Vintage Antique Top Hat and Leather Carrying Case . . D. Magee's Sons Hatters & Furriers, St John, NB. .late 1800's . .RARE . .Free Shipping
Description:
RARE! GENUINE! TOP HAT!  Circa 1890's made by D. Magee's Sons in St. John, New Brunswick, Canada . . With original, hand stitched, leather carry case. 
 
Silk, wool and felt are/were the most common materials used to make these hats.  This hat does have a brush and a perfect concentric pattern on the top, and I've not been able to determine if this is silk plush or genuine beaver felt (neither material is currently available).  From what I've read it takes an expert to tell the difference, however, D. Magee's Sons, in St. John was listed as "Hatters & Furriers" and were in business in the late 1800's 
Hat is in amazing shape for its age . . . exterior is in remarkable shape and the only sign of wear I see is two very small spots on the side where it looks like the nap is worn
Black grosgrain ribbon around the brim . . . brim is firm and contoured with some wear on the very edges . . .  also comes with a wool band that I assume goes over the ribbon
Interior is clean and undamaged and has the makers stamp which reads D. Magee's Sons . . 63 King Street . . St. John, N.B.
shown in photo . . additional photos available upon request
Inner circumference: 22 & 1/2"
The crown rises: 6 & 1/4 inches
Brim extends:  2"
Pristine sweat band,  width: 2 & 1/2"
Comes with leather carry case and velvet dust pillow.  Handle firmly attached with original rivets/stitching.  It appears the  stitching holding the strap to the case has at some point been repaired, but is fully functional . . .  lock still works and key is attached . . . the lid lining has a brown stain as shown in photo
The original leather case has obviously seen some serious miles.  Shipping labels indicate travel to London, Brussels, Budapest, Liverpool, Paris, Charing Cross (via Calais) with the home address in Quebec.  Regardless, it still  keeps the hat snug, safe and protected inside
 
great item of memorabilia from a bygone era 
* * * * * * * * * * FREE SHIPPING - USA ONLY * * * * * * * * * * 
 
I  ship priority mail and include delivery confirmation
* * * * * See store policies for more information * * * * *

Give Your Cat The Gift Of Premium Comfort With a Merino Wool Cat Cave From Meowfia!
Give your cat a cozy new place to call their own! Our 100% Merino wool Cat Caves are designed by cat parents and give cats a comfy space to nap, play and sleep! Cat Caves make perfect presents for your own cats and for all your human friends who love cats!
Each of our Cat Caves is carefully handmade from natural felted wool fibers which are environmentally friendly as well as naturally antibacterial and breathable; they keep cats warm when the weather is cold and cool when it's hot so they are a great alternative to a traditional pet bed! Description:
Amazing LARGE 27" Hippo/ Hippopotamus, garden sculpture.
Due to the fantastic success and popularity of my previous Hippo garden sculpture I decided to create a much larger version of the Hippo. I sculpted the Hippo in the same style as the smaller 17" version I sell so that previous customers can display them together.  Please see my other listings for the smaller 17" Hippo.

With this in mind I created this Hippo sculpture and will create other highly detailed garden sculptures in the future.
As you can see the Hippo looks great in the pictures, I've taken pictures of the Hippo when it's dry and wet so you can see exactly what the colours are like. when the Hippo is wet it looks even more authentic as real hippo's have a shine to their backs when they are submerged in the water. I've also taken some detailed close ups so you can clearly see the texture and quality finish of this garden sculpture.
The Hippo garden sculpture is cast using concrete mixed with fine grain sand for a smoother finish that can take finer detail from the mould.

Product name: Antique Victor Table Top Victrola Model VV-VI in Rare Mahogany Wood
Description: Being offered for sale is a rare Mahogany Victor VV-VI Table Top Victrola.  The Victor company was headquartered in Camden New Jersey, just across the river from Philadelphia.  Based on the Serial number, this machine was produced in 1922.  A great piece of Americana.  Most of the VI models were produced in oak, but this one is a deep rich Mahogany in nice original condition. Product name: Pandora's Dice Tray
Description:
These are wooden dice trays are hand made in the USA. They are intended for use with all forms of dice based games. Be it miniature games, board games, role playing games, or purely dice based games. They also work well as a transport tool for moving models from table to table while gaming, being able to hold entire skirmish sized armies.
The trays are finished in a range of stains, which are sealed in with multiple layers of varnish. The trays are also inlaid with genuine leather bottoms in a range of colors. The edges are all sanded and rounded for a smooth feel and easy handling.
The trays are durable, resistant to scuffing, water resistant, and cleanable. The layers of varnish seal in your chosen stain color and protects the wood from the hazards of use and wear, while also making them easy to clean. Spilled liquids can be cleaned right up without damaging the finish.
The leather inlays help protect the tray and your dice. The leather softens the sound of impacting dice while also protecting them from getting scratched from repeated rolling on textured gaming boards. The leather is cleanable and won't get clotted up or shed like felt can after repeated use.
Each tray also has small rubber feet to raise it up off the tabletop, reduce sliding, and limit wear on the bottom of the tray.
As they are all hand made each tray is unique with slight variations in the build, stain, varnish, and leather inlay. They all have their own unique features and subtle differences.
Outside Tray Dimensions - 6" x 9" X 1 3/4"

With these custom snapchat filters, your guests can take amazing selfies that are branded just for your wedding or event!
Your proof will be sent via an ETSY order conversation within the same or next business day. Once it is finalized, a .PNG will be sent to your email as well and it will be ready to submit to snapchat for review :)

*You will select what you would like the top line of text to read and the middle line font color when you purchase at the drop down menus*
*There is a very subtle black gradient on the bottom of the filter behind the text so the text will show up wonderfully against any photo background!*
*The purchase price includes 2 revision changes. Any changes after that will cost 5 usd per additional proof (unless it is by fault of OnLoveandCoffee) so please check the information you submit carefully :)*
What you will receive is a PNG file that meets Snapchat's guidelines and is 100% ready for submitting/uploading to Snapchat. 
*Please note the below is NOT accepted by snapchat, so please do not include any in notes to seller*
-Hashtags with the # sign
-First AND Last/Middle Names (will not accept both together as this is personal information)
-Cuss Words
Filters also will not work in Mexico!
*Please allow at least 1 business day for your filter to be submitted and reviewed by Snapchat. They will not accept same day submissions. Approval on the weekend does happen, but it can be slower and is risky* 
To let your guests know about the filter at your event, please visit the "Snapchat Filter" section of my shop for various printable/custom sign options!-
https://www.etsy.com/shop/OnLoveandCoffee?ref=hdr_shop_menu§ion_id=19275647
LEARN MORE ABOUT SNAPCHAT GEOFILTERS- 
Please note that there are additional expenses involved when uploading a custom filter to Snapchat. Prices can vary widely depending on size of location and duration. For example, a 20,000 square foot area and 8-hour time period is 5 (which is the minimum dollar amount). When you go to upload your filter, this is a simple & quick process which you will complete online with your Snapchat account. For more information on Snapchat's On-Demand Geofilter program, please visit:
 https://www.snapchat.com/on-demand (this is where you will upload the file) and
https://support.snapchat.com/en-US/a/odg-howto
Once you have your filter all setup with Snapchat, it will then be available during the time and location selected for your event. You need to have your "location settings" enabled for snapchat. To use it, you take the photo on snapchat, then swipe right until you see your custom filter. You can then send the filtered pictures within snapchat or download the image with the filter and repost to various social media sites (Instagram, Facebook, Twitter, etc) or just keep the images as a fun memento of your event!
**This shop is not liable for anything after the snapchat is approved within Snapchat. No refunds will be given after the final snapchat filter is emailed to purchaser**

Product name: If You Love Legos You'll Love the Building Blocks on this Cotton-Poly Fabric, 56" Width - By the Half-Yard or Yard
Description:
Any fabric ordered will be cut from a bolt when it is ordered.
It will be a continuous piece of fabric if you order 1 yard, 2 yards or 5 yards.
The only exception is remnants which is typically the end of a bolt and always clearly marked as such.
No fabric is cut ahead of time.
-_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_-
If you know someone who loves building with Legos then you can probably think of dozens of projects you could do with this fun building block fabric.
The fabric is lightweight, similar to what I would call linen. 
If you would like to receive a small sample of cotton-poly fabric let me know.
The colors are Red, Blue, Light Blue, Yellow and Green.
The pattern repeats every 3 inches vertically and every 3 inches from side to side.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
This fabric can be washed and ironed the same as any other cotton-poly fabric.
I often apply an iron-on interfacing when I need the fabric to have a stiffer feel.
Steam will not hurt the fabric but when ironing it is recommended that steam, or anything above a low heat setting, not be used until after the fabric has been through multiple washing and drying cycles.
______________________________________________________________________
* This fabric is sold by the Half-Yard or Yard.
* Most cotton fabrics are sold as 44 inches wide, this fabric is 56 inches wide not including a sizable selvage.
* Flannel fabrics are sometimes narrower, approximately 42 inches.
* A Fat Quarter of cotton fabric typically measures 18" by 22" but 
   can vary slightly due to the manufacturing process.
* All orders of two or more yards or fat quarters will be cut as one continuous 
   piece unless noted above that the listing consists of multiple remnants.
* If three Fat Quarters are ordered it will be a normal 3/4 yard cut (27 inches).
* Domestic orders of four yards or more will be automatically upgraded to 
   Priority Mail at no additional cost.
______________________________________________________________________
I try my best to keep my listings accurate but I often have more fabric than what the listing indicates.
If you need more than what it says, ask.
I will happily pull the bolt and get an exact measurement for you.
************************************************************************************
If you want to order a larger quantity of fabric, I can typically fit as much as 10 or 11 yards in a Priority Envelope.
It is a more economical shipping method for both Domestic and International buyers.
If interested in ordering a larger quantity of fabrics let me know and I will work it out with you.
************************************************************************************
If you have any questions feel free to contact me via the Convo System here on Etsy, it will get a quicker response than a message sent by email.

Product name: Phoenix Duochrome Color Shifting Top Coat Red to Green Indie Nail Lacquer Starlight Polish Unicorn Pee
Description:
Phoenix is a color shifting duochrome top coat, meant for layering over other polishes.  It is one of Mythological Top Coat trio, which is a set of three color shifting duochrome top coats.  Phoenix shifts from red to gold to green, and flashes vivid red and bright green at the extremes of its color range.  It's beautiful, and pictures don't do justice to the color shift.  The nail wheel swatches show two coats on black.  Phoenix is the shade on the right in the fourth picture.  
NOTE: Due to the limited availability of the pigment used in the Phoenix polishes, there is now a restriction on their purchase. The limit is not more than 30mL per person per 12 month period per individual Phoenix-named polish. The limit is in mL rather than bottles because it applies to both mini bottles and full size bottles. It's 30mL per Phoenix-type polish, so a person could purchase two full size bottles of each Phoenix-named polish in a 12 month period. The polishes that have purchase restrictions are: Phoenix top coat, Phoenix Song top coat, Phoenix Feathers, and Phoenix Fire. This limitation covers individual bottles and sets. For those people interested in doing group orders, contact me first to work something out. If there are any questions or anyone would like more information, please contact me. I'm always happy to explain!
The wonderful Lauren of Dizzy Nails was kind enough to review this polish.  The first picture is a compilation from three of her photos, to show Phoenix at different angles.  The second picture is one of her photos of Phoenix top coat and Unicorn top coat (with Unicorn on the index and ring fingers, and Phoenix on the middle and pinky fingers).  Both pictures show Phoenix over black.  Her photos are fabulous and show the color shift far better than mine.  Please go see her review (and more photos!) here: http://www.dizzynails.com/2012/08/unicorn-and-phoenix.html
The last picture shows what the 15mL and 5mL bottles will look like. I also have the three Mythological Top Coat polishes listed as a set, in both 15mL and 5mL sizes, for less than buying each color individually.
The color shifting pigment in the Phoenix polishes is very similar (and displays a very similar shift) to the pigment in the original elusive unicorn pee.  The pigment in this is the same type of pigment (Polyacrylate-4, red to green shift), but made by a different manufacturer, which results in two minor differences.  The first is that the particle size is not exactly the same.  The second is that the precise spectrum of the color shift and what shade is produced by a particular angle of light are not identical - very, very close, but not identical.  If you have additional questions, or would like the longer and more detailed version of this explanation, please feel free to message me!  
Phoenix is a custom polish, made from scratch with nail lacquer base and color shifting pigment. Starlight Polish is 5 free, meaning free of DBP, toluene, formaldehyde, formaldehyde resin, and camphor, and contains no carmine or other animal-derived pigments.

Shea butter has soothing, moisturizing and protecting effects. Due to the presence of a sizable quantity of unsaponifiable fats, its content in vitamins and other active elements, Shea butter adds other more precise activities to these general properties. It displays a protecting role against UV rays because of its content in cinnamic acid and can thus be incorporated in solar products. The natural latex contained in Shea butter would moreover prevent certain sun allergies. Shea butter also helps cell regeneration and capillary circulation. This favors the healing of small wounds, skin cracks and crevices, and skin ulcers. In the cosmetic field, this property is an asset against skin aging. It has restructuring effects on the epidermis, also on dry and fragile hair. Dry skin, dermatitis, dermatoses, eczema, sun burn, and burns are all helped by natural Shea butter. It has an anti-elastics characteristic which makes it a good active ingredient against stretch marks. Shea butter can also be used to treat rheumatism and aching muscles, and to ease colds because it decongestant nasal mucous tissues. It is very well tolerated by the skin for it does not normally trigger any allergic reaction and can even be used on very sensitive skin areas such as mucous tissues and around the eyes.

Description:
Aluminum keychain hand-stamped with a coordinate of your choice.  It can be stamped on all four sides, but if you're only getting one coordinate, it will only be two sides unless you choose to fill the other sides with something else.
Do you know a location that you want but don't know the coordinates for it or how to find them?  Message us, and we'll find them for you :)
The different Orientation options are as follows:
"Opposite Sides" - This is NOT what is shown in the pictures of this listing.  In this orientation, one coordinate will be stamped on the keychain, and the other one will be stamped on the opposing side.  Only two sides will be stamped.
"Adjacent Sides" - This is what is shown in the picture.  One coordinate on one edge, the other on the edge directly adjacent to it.  Only two sides will be stamped.
"All Four Sides" - In this orientation, the coordinates will be stamped alternating with each other on all four sides.
Looking for something other than coordinates, but still want the bar keychain?  Check out our generic Bar Keychain listing here:
